task.summary: Default task
Solve medium create binary tree from inorder and postorder traversal by fixing the root first and then recursively fixing the root of left/right subarray
Solve medium create binary tree from inorder and preorder traversal by fixing the root first and then recursively fixing the root of left/right subarray
Solve easy find LCA of BST by pruning the search space every step

Solve medium Construct tree from preorder and postorder traversal by fixing one root at a time. Care must be taken to adjust the indices for left/right subarray. I messed up setting up the indices during original attempt
Update documentation on how to think about handling duplicates in ThreeSum

Solve medium Maximum sum of circular subarray by subtracting minimum subarray sum from total sum
Learning -- Circular subarray questions can be solved by filtering out middle elements from the original array, so only wrapped elements remain.

Solve hard Task Scheduler problem, similar to rearrange a string where similar characters are k distance apart
Learning -- New problem, Visualize the problem, once a task is picked it can't be picked up for the next k time. Which task to pick first? In order to solve the answer in minimum cycles, you need to create less holes as possible, which is possible only if you pick most frequent task first, so that you can try to fill the holes with less frequent tasks
Solve medium Bottom left value of a binary tree by DFS and keeping track of the first node of last level

Solve medium set rows and columns of a matrix to 0 if any value in that row and column is 0 by reusing first row and first column as a place for keeping flags.
Learning -- Initially I thought of using the first row and first column by negating the value but it won't work if matrix contains negative number. But placing 0 won't hurt as it's actually a part of the result. So sometimes placing the target result during intermediate operations can help

Solve medium Best time to buy and sell stock with cooldown -- able to solve it in n^2 in my first attempt by leveraging LIS.
Learning -- Think of how to build best result for an index by leveraging results from previous state
Solve medium Construct BST from provided preorder traversal by leveraging the same trick used in validate whether the tree is BST or not (range bound trick)
Solve easy Merge two sorted linked list by keeping a dummy node to append to
Solve medium kth smallest element in M sorted list by using priority queue
Update gotcha in FindMinimumInRotatedSortedArray2

Solve medium whether a sentence is valid or not from the words present in the dictionary.
Learning: My initial approach was very similar to LIS and I generated all the substrings and checked whether they are present in the dictionary or not. However in case when there are few words in the dictionary this won't be efficient. An efficient way would be to iterate over the words in the dictionary and check whether the string starts with any of them. If yes, mark that index. Repeat the process for remaining substring.

Add BFS Logic in PerfectSquares. Similar to WordBreak1
Learning -- In case of problems where you need to find min no of steps required to reach a final state and you are trying to solve it by finding minimum steps to reach previous state, its much optimal to use BFS and directly mark nodes reachable in 1 step from root. Then repeat the same process for the marked nodes.

Solve hard list all ways to break sentence from the words present in the dictionary. Similar to WordBreak1
Learning -- When you want to list all ways to reach a target node from start using BFS, it's better to first check whether we can reach destination or not

Update documentation for storing intermediate results in 2D DP instead of the current 1D DP -- tushar roy rocks
Learning -- Currently not all intermediate results are stored in 1D DP, 2D DP will fix that
Solve easy find winner of array game -- Similar to MajorityElement and PrisonCellAfterNDays

Solve easy DI String Match problem -- Given a string of I and D, need to convert into increasing and decreasing series of 0 and 1, solved it by greedy
Submitted a problem statement as a variant of the problem which generates the minimum pattern

Solve medium construct maximum binary tree -- My initial approach was n^2 but can be optimized by using monotonic stack
Learning -- monotonic stack are very powerful in dealing with problems related to finding greater element
Update problem statement in ZigZagTraversal
Add logic to solve GFG Assembly line scheduling problem via DP

Solve medium Minimum number of adjacent swaps to arrange binary grid by applying swaps from the required row till the first row that satisfies this row count
Learning -- I started trying to solve this problem by applying inversion count and got lost. This does not require inversion count as any row can have more than the number of zeroes required to arrange.

Solve medium find maximum number possible after performing at most one swap in a number
Learning -- Remember to take care of duplicate digits present in a number

Solve hard Get maximum score by using two pointer algorithm to merge two sorted arrays
Learnings -- Had difficulty in traversing both the arrays. DO NOT USE MODULO OPERATOR ON VARIABLES ON WHICH YOU ARE DOING COMPARISON
Solve easy convert sorted array to height balanced BST by fixing middle element as the root
Solve easy find first bad commit version by binary search
Solve easy best time to buy and sell stock with only one transaction allowed by keeping track of the largest number on the right
Update gotcha in ReverseBits
Solve medium Best to time buy and sell stock in multiple transactions
Solve easy pascal's triangle -- question asked in my morgan stanley campus online assessment test
Solve easy find whether number is power of 2, 3 or 4 by checking the location of the set bit

Solve hard find best time to buy and sell stock if allowed to perform at most 2 transactions
Learning -- Did my initial code in n^2 time, similar to longest increasing subsequence.

Solve medium Generate unique bst. Follow up problem to Count unique BST.
Learning -- Was able to figure out the recursion but was not able to figure out how to create new roots. Idea was to create new root for every possible combination of left and right subroots.
Solve easy sort in place even odd array by two pointer approach
Solve easy length of the longest palindrome that can be formed from the existing characters by counting characters with even pairs and single count
Solve medium Vertical order traversal of binary tree using treemap and priority queue to match the desired output
Solve medium generate all root leaf paths in binary tree
Solve medium find all root to leaf path that matches the target sum by backtracking and keeping track of current path

Solve easy but tricky isomorphic strings
Learning -- Read the problem statement carefully you dumb fuck. Initially I completely ignored about the fact that no two characters can have same mapping

Solve medium find smallest string starting from leaf in binary tree by appending current path in a linked list to avoid reversing the path
Learning -- Use linked list wherever we need to reverse the input and index specific access is not required

Solve medium find all root to leaf path sum in binary tree
Learning -- In tree related problems, sometimes we can avoid global variable by relying on results of left and right subtree
Update documentation for logic in FindTwoNonOverlappingSubarrayWithTargetSum
Solve medium Find Kth Bit in Nth String using brute force in contest. Was not able to solve the logic behind offset
Update logic behind finding offset

Solve medium can a string be converted to another string in k moves by shifting characters
Learning -- Handling circular distance was too time consuming for me, got TLE in the first submission because I was looping through the mulipliers for each diff and was checking if that iteration is available and within bounds. Availability was handled by a hashset. Similar to MakingFileNamesUnique

Solve medium find all non overlapping subarray with target sum by keeping track of the last index of the previous valid subarray and making sure that next valid subarray starts >= last index of previous subarray

Solve medium make parantheses valid by adding missing brackets by stack or keeping track of balances
Learning -- In case of making things balanced, instead of using stack, just tracking counter of balance is fast and more effective
